Sending from Bob to Alice and back

Message = I love apples

Steps

  • Bob encrypts the message with Alice's public key and sends the result to Alice
  • Alice decrypts the message with her private key
  • Alice encrypts the message again with her public key and sends the result to Bob
  • Bob decrypts the message with his private key

Step 1

Plain-text message on the Bob's side

cat message.txt

   │ File: message.txt
1  │ I love apples

Bob encrypts using Alice's public key

gpg --recipient alice --encrypt message.txt

Encrypted message on the Bob's side

cat message.txt.gpg

Step 2

Alice decrypts received message using her private key

gpg --decrypt --default-key alice message.txt.gpg

I love apples

Step 3

Alice encrypts the message with Bob's private key

echo 'I love apples' | gpg --recipient bob --encrypt
